  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study will follow a descriptive design involving a survey. Data collection will involve
      paper based questionnaires. The questionnaires have been developed in conjunction with breast
      cancer support groups associated with the Irish Cancer Society and patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of the study is to identify and categorise the need of Metastatic Breast Cancer
      (MBC) patients in Ireland with particular focus on; quality of life, symptom burden and
      access to and value of support available.

      The study also aims to evaluate future service developments that will provide support to
      these patients.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
